HEADWORD: pademelon
<hw>pad`e*mel"on</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any of
several small reddish-brown wallabies of scrubby areas of Australia and
New Guinea, especially those belonging to the genus
<gen>Thylogale</gen>; a paddymelon. See <er>Wallaby</er></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

